author: Hiroyuki Kachi
title: USD/JPY Shows Muted Reaction to Japan Trade Data
text: 0029 GMT [Dow Jones] The USD/JPY showed muted reaction to Japan September trade data and is now at 119.89 compared with around 119.80 before the data. Market participants were monitoring trade data as a downswing in exports could have intensified speculation about BOJ easing at its Oct. 30 policy meeting. But the data (exports +0.6% vs. market consensus of +3.4%) “didn’t turned out to be an incentive strong enough to prompt investors to take positions” in a positive manner, says Mizuho Securities chief FX strategist Kengo Suzuki....
